The paper deals with the task of reusing trained deep network models for comprehensive classification, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a new model-reusing task called knowledge amalgamation, which involves learning a lightweight student model capable of handling comprehensive classification given multiple trained teacher networks. This task involves techniques from several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
